m of the letters surely suggests an earlier date in this range.",-200,-1,"lettering",[443,444],{"_":48,"type":49,"ref":50},{"_":52,"type":53,"ref":54},[446],[57,58],{"_":62,"role":63,"ref":64},{"_":449,"type":201},"24361",{"_":203,"mainLang":204,"languages":451},[203],{"n":70,"url":453,"height":144,"width":145,"desc":146,"surfaceType":75},"ISic001660_tiled.tif",[],[256,456,457,458,459,460,461],"Bulletin épigraphique, 1888-","Manni Piraino, 1963, Due Iscrizioni inedite di Marsala","Wilson, 1990, Sicily under the Roman Empire: the archaeology of a Roman province, 36 B.C. - A.D. 535","Manni Piraino ap. Di Stefano, 1984, Lilibeo. Testimonianze archeologiche dal IV sec a.C. al V sec. d.C.","Di Stefano, 2006, Lilibeo: contributo alla rilettura dell'insula I","Brugnone, 2021, Parlare greco a Lilibeo: la documentazione epigrafica tra II e I sec. a.C.",[259,463,464,465,93,466,467],"77P5MNIR","Q2EG8WCI","VF9MMBI9","CH2A4ZD2","EE9HKNTC",[469,470,471,420,17,21,98,99,100,101,99,102,225,204],"isic001660","i.sicily inscription 001660",{"_":10},"Text encoding: Andoni Llamazares",{"file":474,"uri":474,"title":475,"status":476,"editionAuthor":11,"type":477,"objectType":481,"material":484,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":488,"handNote":492,"date":501,"places":503,"geo":506,"country":59,"region":60,"settlement":52,"repository":508,"idno":509,"textLang":511,"provenance":48,"letterHeights":513,"publications":514,"zotero":524,"keywords":533,"html":104},"ISic001668","A tessera hospitalis recording xenia between Imulch and Lyson",{"_":10},{"_":478,"ana":479,"ref":480},"tessera hospitalis","#function.tessera_hospitalis","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/133.html",{"_":478,"ana":482,"ref":483},"#object.tessera_hospitalis","https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/278.html",{"_":485,"ana":486,"ref":487},"ivory","#material.ivory","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/120.html",{"layout":489},{"p":490,"rs":491,"damage":24},"Four lines of Greek letters, with a consistent left margin, starting at the top of the rear (smooth) side of the tessera, with small vacat below.",{"_":28,"ana":29,"ref":30},{"lettering":493,"dimensions":494},"Small, slightly irregular letters without serifs. Lunate epsilon, sigma and omega; mu formed by four, equal slanting strokes; omicron generally slightly smaller than other letters; beta is closed, but with separated loops; rho is closed; xsi in form of a Z with horizontal cross bar; kappa has short equal length arms.",[495,499],{"type":34,"l":496,"from":36,"to":497,"h":498,"unit":37},"Line 1-4","line4","4-7",{"type":39,"l":500,"from":36,"to":41,"unit":37},"Interlineation",{"_":502,"notBefore":439,"notAfter":440,"evidence":441,"precision":189},"2nd century BCE, or possibly 1st century BCE (the letter forms look more plausibly second than 1st century)",[504,505],{"_":48,"type":49,"ref":50},{"_":52,"type":53,"ref":54},[507],[57,58],{"_":62,"role":63,"ref":64},{"_":510,"type":201},"4522",{"_":203,"mainLang":204,"languages":512},[203],[],[256,456,515,516,517,518,519,520,521,522,523],"Franz, 1853, CIG","Kaibel, 1890, IG","Paciaudi, 1751, Diatribe qua Graeci anaglyphi interpretatio traditur","Castelli, 1753, Storia di Alesa, antica città di Sicilia","Castelli, 1762, Le antiche iscrizioni di Palermo","Salinas, 1873, Del Real Museo di Palermo, relazione","Brugnone, 1984, Lilibeo. Testimonianze archeologiche dal IV sec a.C. al V sec. d.C.","Ampolo, 2012, Compresenza di ethne e culture diverse nella Sicilia occidentale. Per una nuova prospettiva storica","Brugnone, 2024, Lilibeo e il Mare. Il museo archeologico regionale di Marsala",[259,463,525,526,527,528,529,530,93,531,532],"TQMVHEVL","Q2SBPG9F","ES9C5XT6","U7S4ZAG3","4JP8QJ5H","DTXHQTEA","TWMDKTFT","H5GJ8WQW",[534,535,536,478,478,485,98,99,100,101,99,102,225,204],"isic001668","a tessera hospitalis recording xenia between imulch and lyson",{"_":10},{"file":538,"uri":538,"title":539,"status":540,"editionAuthor":11,"type":541,"objectType":542,"material":546,"condition":548,"layoutDesc":550,"handNote":553,"date":558,"places":562,"geo":565,"country":59,"region":60,"settlement":52,"repository":567,"idno":568,"textLang":569,"facsimile":571,"provenance":48,"letterHeights":576,"publications":577,"zotero":579,"keywords":581,"html":104},"ISic003070","I.Sicily inscription 003070",{"_":10},{"_":163,"ana":164,"ref":165},{"_":543,"ana":544,"ref":545},"column","#object.funerary_monument.column","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/100",{"_":547,"ana":172},"Plaster on stone",{"ana":549},"#condition.damaged",{"layout":551},{"rs":552,"damage":24},{"_":177,"ana":178,"ref":179},{"lettering":554,"dimensions":555},"Neatly painted square letters with short serifs, painted in the style of stone cut letters. Alpha is broad with straight bar; Epsilon has equal length horizontal strokes; theta is ovoid with a full horizontal bar; kappa has arms that are not quite ful length; mu has vertical first and last, with middle strokes nearly reaching down to the line; pi has equal length verticals; sigma is four-bar, of equal length, top and bottom strokes horizontal.",[556,557],{"type":34,"l":35,"from":36,"to":36,"unit":37},{"type":39,"l":40,"from":36,"to":41,"unit":37},{"_":559,"notBefore":439,"notAfter":560,"evidence":561,"precision":189},"2nd century BCE (Manni Piraino)",-101,"archaeological-context",[563,564],{"_":48,"type":49,"ref":50},{"_":52,"type":53,"ref":54},[566],[57,58],{"_":62,"role":63,"ref":64},{"type":201},{"_":203,"mainLang":204,"languages":570},[203],{"n":70,"url":572,"height":573,"width":574,"desc":575,"surfaceType":75},"ISic003070_tiled.tif","5789px","3861px","Photo R.J.A. Wilson",[],[256,256,85,578,213],"Manni Piraino, 1987, Marsala",[259,259,93,580,218],"5G8I6FZF",[582,583,584,163,543,171,98,99,100,101,99,102,225,204],"isic003070","i.sicily inscription 003070",{"_":10},{"file":586,"uri":586,"title":587,"status":588,"editionAuthor":11,"type":589,"objectType":590,"material":592,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":593,"handNote":601,"date":605,"plac